INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(70540, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Finally! It\'s like trying to craft with two hands tied behind my back without those things.\n\nHere, take these schematics. I bet there\'s something in there you didn\'t know.', 47187), -- An Engineer's Best Friend
(70617, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, yes, yes! This is exactly what I needed.\n\nTake my field notes when you go--I\'ve written down some useful information about the mining process here in the Isles.', 47187), -- All Mine, Mine, Mine
(66464, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are quite the impressive and fearsome combatant. The centaurs are in awe of you. Gurgthock is fuming for not betting his farm on you instead of Amaa. You win the grand prize.', 47187), -- The Field of Ferocity: Master of the Hunt!
(66463, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I now understand the rumors I have heard about you and your crew. You have gotten further than I would have ever expected.', 47187), -- The Field of Ferocity: Elemental Revenge Round!
(66462, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '... Wuzzat? Is the fight over? I think I fell asleep in the middle of it for some reason.\n\nI\'m guessing you won if you\'re standing in front of me?', 47187), -- The Field of Ferocity: Lost in the Dream!
(66461, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a show! I could feel sparks flying from here!', 47187), -- The Field of Ferocity: Foe from the Volcano!
(66460, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m glad you dealt with that as quickly as you did. The stench was starting to reach the podium here.', 47187), -- The Field of Ferocity: Lord of Decay!
(66339, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With this victory, you have helped the Maruuk more than you will ever know. Our most sincere thanks, $n. Go with the blessings of Ohn\'ahra.', 46924), -- The Nokhud Offensive: The Wind Belongs to the Sky
(72135, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These items are wonderful! There is a trove of information here to study!', 46924), -- Neltharus: Secrets Within
(66119, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our home will bear the wounds of this assault for years, but we are strong. We will endure... and the eggs we saved will bring about a bright future for us all.\n\nThank you.', 46924), -- Ruby Life Pools: Primalist Invasion
(71238, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is this about the posters? Did they actually work?!', 46924), -- The Ruby Feast!
(66211, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Iskaara would be lost without you.', 46924), -- Brackenhide Hollow: To the Source
(66868, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful! Though not specifically something of Tyr\'s, this will still make a fascinating addition to the Archives.', 46924), -- Preserving the Past: Legacy of Tyr
(70741, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is very kind of you to gather these items. We will return them to their owners right away!', 46924), -- Some Favorite Things
(69934, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Szareth wants to heal everyone, no matter the consequences. Rebels, Scalesworn, wildlife: each deserves equal care.\n\nAnd while I might find Szareth\'s idealism galling, Gelikyr depends on their expertise.\n\nSo my thanks to Szareth--and you as well. These potions will be invaluable.', 46924), -- Bleeding Hearts
(65920, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work, $p. The wards have been restored, and Tyrhold Reservoir is once again protected. Thank you for all you have done. Thaldraszus owes you a great debt.', 46924), -- For the Ward!
(65921, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will always feel pain for those we lost, but I am thankful for the ones we rescued.', 46924), -- Refti Retribution
(65916, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. Our final task of restoring the wards awaits.', 46924), -- We Don't Negotiate with Primalists
(65918, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p. That should hold them at bay for now.', 46924), -- Preventative Maintenance
(70139, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As I suspected. It is imperative that we find the missing keystones.\n\nOtherwise the losses that Zuttiki and I have suffered would be for nothing.', 46924), -- Where There's a Ward, There's a Way
(65913, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $r. Were it not for your aid, I would have surely perished.', 46924), -- Wotcher, Watcher?
(70885, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, $c. You\'ve proved your worth to the Valdrakken Accord. Here are some supplies to help you aid our cause. Don\'t let us down!', 46924), -- Renown Supplies
(66891, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This ash could provide the essential component in a variety of machines that would improve the lives of people across Azeroth. But who am I kidding? We\'re going to make explosives with it. BOOM!', 46924), -- Explosive Ash
(70179, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh bother, these are quite a bit more crumbly than I was expecting. They look quite a lot more solid when they are launched at your head! \n\nWell. I\'m sure I can use these for building regardless, thank you for your help! \n\nMaybe there are some mud elementals around here somewhere I can use to glue it together....', 46924), -- A Two for One Deal
(71034, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ooo, a new artifact. Let me log it in the ledger and note you returned it. \n\n<Cataloger Jakes makes a notation in her ledger.> \n\nGot it! Keep them coming!', 46924), -- Dragon Isles Artifacts
(29593, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! The long term effects of this attack will be far worse than slaying a few orcs could ever be.', 46924), -- Hitting Them Where It Hurts
(29530, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. We need the time you\'ve bought us to investigate this link between the fel orcs and the Burning Legion. You very well may have saved hundreds of lives through your actions.', 46924), -- Demons in the Citadel
(29527, 396, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With their leadership dead their forces should be in disarray.$B$BBut there\'s far more to this than killing a few guards, $c.', 46924), -- War on the Ramparts
(62265, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back to the present! There\'s a lot you have to do.', 46924), -- A New Adventure Awaits
(71060, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your deeds honor your people, friend $n. Please accept this helm as a gift in recognition of all that you do for us. \n\nShould you find yourself wanting more, I would be happy to trade with you.', 46879), -- To Adorn Your Head
(70928, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Clan Shikaar knows a great hunting trophy when we see one. This will earn you much favor in our eyes.', 46879), -- Hunting Trophy
(72868, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Only the greatest of hunters can boast of this many great hunting trophies. You honor our hunt.', 46879), -- More Hunting Trophies
(72363, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, dragonrider. Welcome back. Here\'s some dust. No, I don\'t know what it really is either. The Ohn\'ir mystics say it\'s supposed to help you commune with our ancestors. That the ancestors are all around us. Seems optimistic, if you ask me.\n\nI can\'t claim to understand the Ohn\'iri. The sky\'s honest truth is that I don\'t really want to. They\'re good people, mostly, but they\'re strange. Unnerving. But also allies, and they asked me to give it to you. And to make more available if you want it. So I do.', 46879), -- Good at Doings, Not Understandings
(66676, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve returned! Look--Lizi is going to be all right.', 46879), -- Sneaking In
(65711, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Radiya is unusually quiet and trembling slightly as she looks upon the tortured beast.>', 46879), -- Stealing Its Thunder
(65761, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$p!', 46879), -- More Adventure Than Expected
(65770, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Togotseng\'s ohuna glares at you.>', 46879), -- A Promise Is A Promise
(65907, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Seems like they like you! Or just the fruit. That\'s okay too. <Radiya winks.>', 46879), -- Favorite Fruit
(66657, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Unlike my mother, and our ancestors, no one will wish for Arban to live again. Thank you for helping me avenge them.', 46879), -- And Stay Dead!
(66656, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m so relieved that my mother is at peace again. Thank you, $n!', 46879), -- Definitely Eternal Slumber
(69936, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An initiate must not take pleasure in the death of another Maruuk. But Zambul makes that a challenge.', 46879), -- Zambul, Head Vandal
(66655, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! I should be able to use these to release them from the Ukhel. Then they can return to the rest they deserve.', 46879), -- Reagents of De-Necromancy
(66654, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a good start. I can use these weapons to free their owners... I hope.', 46879), -- Desecrator Annihilator
(66652, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'This spear... it belonged to my mother, Cathan. She was a great hunter. When she got sick, I... I couldn\'t save her.\n\nLike all great Maruuk centaur, she was buried with her weapon. But this means the Ukhel are using these weapons to raise spirits and bind them to their service - including my mother!', 46879), -- Return to Mender
(66651, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Clan Ukhel dishonors itself with dark magic. Now they have moved into the kurgans with their Nokhud allies. Neither clan should be here! I\'ve been watching from here, where I\'m safely out of sight.', 46879), -- Up to No-khud
(70070, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'He was swallowed by the--\n\nFirequackers still has much to learn. \n\nPilot on the other hand has already taken a liking to you. The smartest of the brood and the one most ready to leave. \n\nFor all that you have done, I thank you! Take care of my sweet duckling!', 46879), -- But... I Am the Hero of Ducks
(70069, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My beautiful ducklings! You look so strong!\n\nPilot, come. Play time is over. \n\n<Pilot refuses to leave your side and tries to hide behind your legs. Until Gracus scoops her up.> \n\nSeems she likes you.', 46879), -- Others Call Me Duck Herder
(70062, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh...  Back so soon?  It only felt like a moment. \n\nYou got the good parts as well!\n\nFirequackers and Pilot are going to love the chitin.', 46879), -- Some Call Me Bug Catcher
(66700, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This was found at the Nelthazan Ruins? Fascinating. \n\nIts markings are ancient, but they bear a resemblance to other artifacts we have discovered in and around the ancient machinations of Deathwing.\n\nFurther study is necessary.', 46879), -- The Black Locus
(65898, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p.\n\nYou have been most helpful.', 46879), -- Proto Problems
(65895, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have seen a sickness like this once before in my life. I had hoped to never see it again.', 46879), -- Competing Company
(65893, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They are still looking for something? Then why did you bring me this garbage?\n\nWe have to find it before they do!', 46879), -- The Relic Inquiry
(65891, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will gather everything in time.', 46879), -- Tools of the Tirade
(65890, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well of course I am shouting! The book will not listen. What else am I to do?', 46879), -- The Nelthazan Ruins
(71058, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, you are a dragonrider, yes? You show great promise as an ally.\n\nLet me give you this, then, to celebrate our growing alliance. And I promise there is more where that came from!', 46879), -- Observing the Wind
(67298, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Huh, this is really interesting! I guess you never know where you\'ll find knowledge.\n\nKeep an eye out for any treasures like this. Maybe there will be more wisdom to find in the world.\n\nAnd thanks for seeing this vista with me. It\'s really spectacular, isn\'t it?', 46879), -- The Wonders of the World
(70721, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p.\n\nDawa and I will always remember what you have done for us.', 46879), -- After My Ohn Heart
(70730, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Arbhog\'s horns? They\'ll do just fine.\n\nArbhog was once the mightiest musken on the plains. These are a fitting gift for the mightiest hunter. I am sure Narman will appreciate them.\n\nPerhaps one day he will teach me to hunt. An Ohn\'ir huntsman. Ha! Imagine that.', 46879), -- Shikaar Giver
(70501, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! You are ready to join the Grand Hunts! \n\nPlease inform this Nesingwary Jr. that there is more to hunting than mindless killing and that he is unwelcome to join us.', 46879), -- License to Hunt
(70337, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s this?\n\nHow fascinating. It must be an ancient artifact of great importance.\n\nWe will need some time to study it.', 46879), -- Emberwatch
(71231, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Dragonrider! Your aid will be welcome in the coming hunts.', 46879), -- Call of the Hunt
(69096, 2, 0, 0, 0, 20, 0, 0, 0, '<Selbekh\'s eyes still glisten with tears.>\n\nTaivan... So this is his true gift. \n\nHow could I have been so blind? He is different from other bakar, yes, but he has proven himself a valuable member of Clan Teerai. He will stay by my side for the rest of his days, rescuing who he can, and healing who I cannot.\n\nPlease, come and visit us anytime you\'d like! We are both truly grateful for all you have done for us!', 46879), -- Taivan's Purpose
(69095, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'And here we are. Home again, safe and sound.\n\nI can\'t begin to express how grateful I am that you and Taivan arrived when you did. You saved many lives today!', 46879), -- Homeward Hound
(69094, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That... that seems to be everyone!\n\nTaivan! That was incredible! I had no idea he had this in him!', 46879), -- Saving Centaur
(68087, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, $n! Thank Ohn\'ahra the messenger found you. We have our hands full here!', 46879), -- Danger in Daruukhan
(71022, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That could have gone better. Sorry, friend, but I don\'t think Taivan is cut out for this. \n\nHe\'s a very nice bakar, but doesn\'t quite seem smart enough to figure out how to get the argali into the pen, or aggressive enough to take command of the herd away from the ram. \n\nI\'m afraid I\'m going to have to send you back to Selbekh with bad news.', 46879), -- Reign of the Ram
(68085, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hmm... Taivan still seems confused. He just doesn\'t seem to be grasping this.\n\nYou did great, though! Are you in the market for a new career?', 46879), -- Shaping a Shepherd
(70739, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I would sooner ask all the stars of the night sky to admire me back than claim to be wholly worthy of Dawa\'s love.\n\nNonetheless, I will find the courage to proceed. When the time comes, will you assist me with a grand proposal?', 46879), -- Bloodlines, Sweets, and Teerai
(70187, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Patience, young one. There is still much to learn.\n\nBut you may celebrate today, for you understand more than you did before.', 46879), -- Specialized Secrets: Engineering
(69979, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The path to mastery is slow but steady. Honor the journey.\n\nIf you seek additional wisdom, continue the good hunt. There will always be quests in the world, creatures to hunt and learn from.\n\nAnd I shall be here to help you understand the knowledge you gain.', 46879), -- A Worthy Hunt
(68084, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well hello there, newcomer. What can I do for you and your very large friend?', 46879), -- The Gentle Giant
(66459, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve done well, for the first ladder. But we\'re just warming up. Speak with Gurgthock again when you\'re ready to move on to the second round.', 46879), -- The Field of Ferocity: Terror of the Swamp!
(70444, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey, you\'re no centaur.\n\nEhh. You\'ll do.', 46879), -- The Fields of Ferocity
(69946, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you truly seek my knowledge, you must prove yourself worthy of it.', 46879), -- The Master of Their Craft
(68083, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Taivan just returned. They could not have trained him so quickly could they? No... I suppose not.\n\n<She sighs deeply and looks at Taivan.>\n\nHe doesn\'t seem to be taking it well, either. I have one more idea, and if this doesn\'t work, we will have to make some difficult decisions.', 46879), -- Try Again, Taivan!
(70989, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jadar shakes his head.>\n\nVery disappointing. I\'m afraid Taivan just does not have it in him to hunt like a Shikaar. Even with other bakar fighting beside him, he could not shake his unwillingness to attack his enemy. \n\nWhat a waste!', 46879), -- Part of a Pack
(67921, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your bakar, while massive and strong, does not seem to have the will to do what needs to be done in the hunt. He is too soft!\n\nI will give him one more chance, but this is it!', 46879), -- The Hunting Hound
(71035, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at all these artifacts! This might take a minute. \n\n<Cataloger Jakes hastily makes several notes in her ledger.> \n\nGot it! Off with you, now! Come back if you have more!', 46879), -- Multiple Dragon Isles Artifacts
(72876, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at all these artifacts! This might take a minute. \n\n<Cataloger Jakes hastily makes several notes in her ledger.> \n\nGot it! Off with you, now! Come back if you have more!', 46879), -- Multiple Dragon Isles Artifacts
(71004, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Not sure I see what all the fuss is about with this one. Feels like every other dirty hunk of rock I\'ve held before.\n\nOh well, I\'ll ensure this is properly documented, researched, and archived for the expedition.', 46879), -- Wanted: Ohuna Mass-Binding Totem
(65837, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Tirren? He\'s still hoofing around, is he?\n\nThank you for coming. We can use all the help we can get.', 46879), -- Trouble In The Pines
(65901, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whew, thank you! Freedom!', 46879), -- Sneaking Out
(67772, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What brings you to the Shikaar hunting grounds, stranger?\n\nThe Teerai would like us to train your bakar as a hunter? We do not usually accept such requests from other clans, but I will consider it. Her gift is quite generous, and a fully-trained beast of his size would be a sight to behold. I bet he could take down a bull mammoth all on his own!\n\nHmm... I will have to see him in action before I make my decision.', 46879), -- The Trouble with Taivan
(70929, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Only the greatest of hunters can boast of this many great hunting trophies. You honor our hunt.', 46879), -- More Hunting Trophies
(72117, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Outsider, you are proving yourself useful. Let this warm you on cold nights. And when it does, remember that we are friends.\n\n<Huseng grins.>\n\nI see you doing great things for our people, $n.', 46879), -- Cultural Exchange
(65796, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, this will give me some peace of mind as we prepare for our journey.', 46879), -- The Best Defense...
(65789, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I thank you. These will be put to good use.', 46879), -- Where Rivers Sleep
(66698, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you. Our clan deeply appreciates the assistance.', 46879), -- Counting Argali
(65792, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The clan will be talking about this for weeks!', 46879), -- Teeth for a Tooth
(66864, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What\'s that you\'ve found? Give it here!\n\nYes... this will do quite nicely...\n\nFor our research, of course. Now go--and thank you.', 46879), -- Relic Recovery: Brackenhide Hollow
(72192, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Halls of Infusion are once again safe thanks to your assistance, $n.', 46879), -- Halls of Infusion: Entropy to Order
(72193, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It seems you had an eventful first day. It\'s a good thing you\'re accustomed to the unexpected.', 46879), -- The Algeth'ar Academy
(66998, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for a moment\'s respite. A caretaker\'s work is never done.', 46879), -- Fighting Fire with... Water
(67094, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, how wonderful! I bet they all have smiles on their cute little faces, beaks, snouts and whatnot. \n\nThere is one more critter that needs our help, though, and I fear the situation is rather dire.', 46879), -- A Dryad's Work Is Never Done
(70126, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Take these finishing reagents. Use them to increase your crafting skill when you really need something high quality.\n\nBe kind and respectful to your customers and they will honor you with their business, $p.', 46879), -- A Finishing Touch
(67295, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. If you ever have questions about specializations, you can always talk to me again.\n\nNow go out and hone your talents! Oh, and take this with you. I found it on my travels.\n\nThere is something mysterious about it. Perhaps the knowledge contained within can further your specialization training.\n\nThomas was telling me he met a master artisan the other day. Perhaps this master could help you unlock the secrets within?', 46879), -- That's My Specialty
(70221, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hey there $p! The Artisan\'s Consortium would like to thank you for everything you\'ve done for us. We\'d like to give you some Artisan\'s Mettle free of charge.\n\nMaybe use it to fill some recrafting orders for us!', 46879), -- Show Your Mettle
(67093, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Nozdormu peers searchingly at the sphere as you hand it over. The sands inside brighten and swirl under his touch.>\n\nI had thought this to be lost in this timeline. Nothing ever remains so, it seems.', 46879), -- An Anomalous Shrine
(66412, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m jealous of him, if I\'m being honest. To be young again, and exploring the world. You\'ll have to visit, sometime, so you can tell me what he\'s been up to.', 46879), -- Carry On, Basilton
(66139, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Incredible! I wasn\'t sure it was going to work, but I\'m glad it did.', 46879), -- Flame at Last
(66137, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The elemental problem is more dire than I thought, if you killed that many. Alexstrasza will be happy, at least.', 46879), -- Lashing Out
(66136, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent! This is just what we need to snuff out those fire elementals once and for all.', 46879), -- Elemental Extract
(66138, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work.  Nozdormu informed me yesterday that he wishes to express his gratitude.', 46879), -- Like Sands Through the Hourglass
(66279, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $p.  Nozdormu will be pleased to have this returned.', 46879), -- New Kid on the Clock
(66135, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, there he is! My lovely assistant. Who\'s a good boy? A good, spiky boy? Basilton! Who\'s the spikiest? That\'s right! You are!\n\nAhem. Thank you, $p.', 46879), -- The Gardener's Apprentice
(67154, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An unexpectedly large haul. Perhaps those rifts are causing more trouble than we calculated.', 46879), -- Entropic Remnants
(71227, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another challenger? Welcome! \n\nAerial Challenges are timed races on courses throughout the Dragon Isles. Beat track times to earn your rank.', 46879), -- Aerial Challenges
(66465, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Passage will be a far safer place without those poisoned spears to worry about.\n\nYou have kept a lot of people safe with your deeds this day, $n. The Waywatchers - and I - owe you a great debt.', 46879), -- Cache and Release
(66467, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. The Embertooth\'s venom harvesting days should be behind them now that they have been deprived of their source.\n\nI realize now that I don\'t have to be a Waywatcher to make a difference in the world. I am going to resign my post and commit myself to my art. Hopefully some day I will be able to depict the most beautiful vistas in the Dragon Isles, for all the world to see.\n\nI just hope my sister understands.', 46879), -- Art Imitates Life
(66457, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With Bluescale taken care of, I doubt we will have to deal with any organized tarasek encroachment any time soon.\n\nNow all that\'s left is to deal with the poison.', 46879), -- Ending the Blue Period
(66456, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Alvi takes the spears that you gathered. She carefully scrapes her dagger across one of the blades, removing a film of sticky, sickly sap.>\n\nIt\'s just as I thought. Thank you, $n. This should be enough for an antidote, and I even think I know where the poison is coming from.', 46879), -- A Poisonous Palette
(66230, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah... You really did find it.\n\nIn truth, it\'s more of a sketchbook than a ledger. For as long as I can remember, I\'ve been more interested in doodling than scouting...\n\n<Alvi looses a long, low sigh.>\n\nMaybe if I had actually done my job properly, then Nori wouldn\'t have gotten hurt.\n\nI have to fix this... but I don\'t know if I can do it alone.', 46879), -- A Sketchy Request
(66472, 1, 0, 0, 0, 600, 0, 0, 0, '<Thadezus pauses for an uncomfortable amount of time.>\n\nAllis and I had bets on if you would be successful, $c\n\n I am glad that you were.', 46879), -- Primal List
(66473, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for everything you have done for us, $c.', 46879), -- The Land Awakens
(66471, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is just what we needed.', 46879), -- Prime Planning
(66470, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Looks like you made it in one piece.', 46879), -- The Forward Push
(66278, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This was in the shed? It\'s not mine, but I think I remember who it belongs to.', 46879), -- One Drakonid's Junk
(66134, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank the Titans you showed up! Otherwise I don\'t know if I\'d ever get these pests to leave.\n\nSo what do you say to helping an old Drakonid out with the rest of the gardens?', 46879), -- Azeroth Pest Control
(70883, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A garden keeper needs their own weapons. Let me outfit you for battle. \n\nI have more tools of war if you need. I appreciate your help taming these wilds!', 46879), -- A Hand in Cultivation
(71229, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your aid is welcome, Dragonrider. There is much to be done around our camp.', 46879), -- Call of the Plains
(72157, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect. Just what I needed.\n\nTake these old field notes. There must be something in there that will teach you about mining.', 46879), -- -Unknown-
(70750, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Yes, indeed I am impressed, friend. As a representative of the Accord I can assure you your work has not gone unnoticed!\n\nPlease, accept this on behalf of our allies.', 46879), -- Aiding the Accord
(71210, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Another battle is won, but the war continues.', 46879), -- To Dragonbane Keep!
(72448, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done! I knew I could count on you, friend.', 46879), -- Securing Our Legacy
(72337, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This key will allow us to access more of the Citadel\'s lost secrets.', 46879), -- Greater Obsidian Key
(72246, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the Serene Dreams Spa! With us, you may partake of many relaxing activities!\n\nOh! Are you here to help? I would be honored to have your assistance.', 46879), -- Serene Dreams
(72067, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How delightful. I am so glad you\'re joining us! However, we could really use some help.', 46879), -- Relaxation Time!
(67007, 6, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, '<Kemora turns gracefully to address you. Before speaking, with a smile upon her face, her eyes follow your being from the ground upon which you walk moving upward, slowly, until your eyes meet in a calming gaze.>\n\nIs it answers you seek as well, $r?\n\nI am ready to speak if you are up for the challenge.', 46879), -- Archival Assistance
(70879, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back, $n.\n\nMy eyes and ears have just told me the good news.', 46879), -- Report on the Rebels
(70938, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you ready to make magic, adventurer? \n\nNo, I don\'t mean that hand wavy stuff some like to make. I mean the mystical aroma arts, the deep knowledge of ingredients and flavor, and the way a soup speaks to you to let you know what it needs. Is that you salivating? No? Must be me. \n\nLet\'s get cooking!', 46801), -- Community Feasts
(69983, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This may be important. Thank you for bringing it to us, $n.', 46801), -- Flamecarved Bone
(66468, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sharnax stares down at you.>\n\nHmm... It appears you are someone with more skill than the commander had originally assumed.\n\nThere is more to be done before the day is over.', 46801), -- What Once Was Ours
(66100, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n, but we have bigger things to worry about now.', 46801), -- Supplying in Weight
(66448, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, gracious, a traveler. Please forgive me, I am a bit of a mess at the moment.', 46801), -- The Wayward Waywatcher
(70878, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nicely done, $n!\n\nMaldra shared with me the details of your heroics.', 46801), -- Ring of Fire
(70876, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Without those foci, the rebels will no longer be able to imbue their runestones with explosive flame.', 46801), -- Fracture the Foci
(70875, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n.\n\nThose who follow the Primalists cannot be allowed to spread chaos and destruction.', 46801), -- Worst of the Worst
(70874, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Worry not. That chilly, damp feeling is temporary.', 46801), -- To Breach a Fire Wall
(70873, 1, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, 0, '<Maldra examines the Fallingwater Motes.>\n\nYes, these should do nicely.', 46801), -- Chasing Waterfalls
(70850, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am indebted to you for rescuing my friend.', 46801), -- Maldra's in Hot Water
(70843, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I could feel the tremor of those explosions all the way from here!\n\nValdrakken is now safer, thanks to your efforts.', 46801), -- Ruin the Runestones
(70842, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will send word to step up our security measures in these locations.', 46801), -- Detonation Locations
(70838, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You handled yourself well.\n\nThese rebels are no slouches.', 46801), -- Rebels With a Cause
(70837, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'This is definitely a base of operations.\n\nThe Misty Vale is crawling with rebels... and Primalists!', 46801), -- Follow the Clues
(66299, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Things didn\'t go exactly to plan, but no good Goblin scheme ever does! Nice work!\n\nThere will still be Screechflight here, but they\'ll be easier to cull without their Matriarch organizing their efforts. And the Bluefeathers will actually have a chance to survive.\n\nHarpies and dragons aren\'t that different. Forgetting their attempted mass digestion of the cliffside, they\'re akin to a civilization of their own. Maybe there\'s a peaceful brood out there? \n\nOh, and keep the disguise. Looks good on you.', 46801), -- The Awaited Egg-splosion
(65778, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did great and looked pretty good in that outfit to boot!\n\nFinally ready to cut this terrifying threat off at its beak?', 46801), -- Screechflight Potluck
(65287, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is more than I imagined you\'d be able to recover!\n\nMaybe you\'re not a bad sort after all. Not that I was thinking that or anything!', 46801), -- Separating the Yolk
(65371, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Perfect! And a little gross. Just as I planned.\n\nTime to craft a disguise and take this matriarch out to roost!', 46801), -- A Nest of Our Own
(65374, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is more than enough feathers! And all collected without the Feather-Plucker exploding... right?', 46801), -- It's Plucking Time
(65490, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, yes! Quality stuff!!\n\nHave you thought about doing this work professionally, $n?', 46801), -- Explosive Excrement
(65475, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ho, now! That\'s certainly no dinner menu you\'re holding!\n\nOr maybe it is...', 46801), -- Rolling in the Screech
(65313, 641, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My fine-tuned bird senses are telling me these Screechflight aren\'t just here for snacks...\n\nBut you did well, $n! Let me decipher this scroll and we\'ll find out just what these harpies are after.', 46801), -- A Roc-ing Appetite
(65373, 4, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Oh, thank the flights!\n\nI\'ve come to like the professor, and this could have spelled the end of our new friendship!', 46801), -- Plucking Parts
(65267, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n!\n\nI\'ve been assisting the good Professor while you\'ve been gone. I\'m afraid to say I\'ve made things worse for her...', 46801), -- Smash 'Em to Feathereens
(66071, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A full-feathered job, $n!\n\nI would have helped you with the healing and the slaying, but I\'m more of an \'ideas goblin\' these days.', 46801), -- Flying Rocs
(70781, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Some guard in Gelikyr told you I\'d be here? Did they say I own \'em any money?', 46801), -- Out of the Blue
(69933, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The lasher attacked you?\n\n<Szareth frowns, sniffing at your clothes. Their snout wrinkles in disgust.>\n\nNo wonder--you reek of blood. And not yours, I assume.\n\nWar truly engulfs the Isles.', 46801), -- Curiosity's Price
(69932, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Szareth takes the extra pollen and linens, then looks toward their hut.>\n\nDucks have to contend with harpies further up the cliffside. The wounded land here, and I aid them how I can.\n\nI hope this one will make it.', 46801), -- Every Life Counts
(72585, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve met everyone? Excellent. Maybe they will stop sending me emissaries, then. \n\nI hope you will continue to strengthen the bonds you have made with these communities. You have only to benefit each other.', 46801), -- Open Orientation
(72435, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you have a pleasant time in Iskaara. \n\nAs you know now, many us are fine craftsmen and merchants. I encourage you to continue to ask around and learn what all of my people have to offer.', 46801), -- Orientation: Iskaara
(70722, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Make sure to summon Lubbins, then use this battle-stone on him. It\'ll permanently make him stronger.', 46801), -- What Lubbins Needs
(70697, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Jyhanna sent you to the right Tuskarr, $n. We\'ll get Lubbins back to his old self in no time!', 46801), -- An Expert Opinion
(72397, 6, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Met me Granpap, did ye?\n\nWell, don\'t believe all his stories... He loves to brag about the family!', 46801), -- Orientation: Dragonscale Basecamp
(72399, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'d better not have trampled any of my plants with those clumsy stompers of yours. Now, what do you want from me?', 46801), -- The Hermit's Garden
(71179, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Thadezus sighs deeply.>\n\nYou are telling me that Drine sent you?', 46801), -- Look to the Overlook
(70647, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. I am so relieved to see little Lubbins safe and sound.\n \nOh! He seems to have taken a liking to you!', 46801), -- Oh Where, Oh Where Can He Be?
(70882, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, $c. You\'ve proved your worth to the Valdrakken Accord. Here are some supplies to help you aid our cause. Don\'t let us down!', 46801), -- Renown Supplies
(71024, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'I am grateful Captain Drine sent you to help.\n\nYou have keen eyes and are resourceful.', 46801), -- Chaos and Commotion
(70839, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have spent all of my time since the waking studying the titans. Their history is fascinating. What power they must have wielded to create the dragonflights! There is so much knowledge to be gained about them! \n\nIf you could bring me any titan relics you find around the Dragon Isles, I will put in a good word for you with the Valdrakken Accord.', 46801), -- The Search for Titan Relics
(70840, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Amazing! This relic is perfectly preserved. I will begin studying it right away.\n\nYour efforts are most appreciated! I will remember my promise to speak well of you to the Valdrakken Accord. \n\nNow, where was I? Yes, this will fit in right over here...', 46801), -- A Titan Relic
(69919, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great, great, great! Keep it up. There\'s always more orders to fill!', 46801), -- A Craft in Need
(72783, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<You can return to any Crafting Order representative to put in more orders for new equipment as long as you have the components!>', 46801), -- Crafting Orders
(70633, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A Spark of Ingenuity. An item that can unlock potential unheard of since the time of Tyr himself.\n\nI am sure you shall use it wisely.', 46801), -- Fueling the Engine
(70182, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can you feel the potential emanating from the bottle?', 46801), -- The Sweet Taste of Victory
(70181, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Admirably done. You have earned your reward.', 46801), -- First Challenge of Tyr: Finesse
(70845, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<It feels as if the statue reacts to your presence, its mechanism slowly awakening and coming to life.>', 46801), -- In Tyr's Footsteps
(70180, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What power do you seek?', 46801), -- Jump-Start? Jump-Starting!
(72773, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nice to meetcha. We could use another pair of hands figuring out how to kickstart this thing.', 46801), -- Learning Ingenuity
(72406, 6, 11, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'On behalf of the Valdrakken Accord, we look forward to working with you, $p.', 46801), -- Orientation: Valdrakken
(71232, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you, $n. \n\nThere are many sources of power within the Dragon Isles, as long as you know where to look!', 46801), -- Renown of the Dragon Isles
(66221, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '$n, please accept our most sincere gratitude for all you have done for us. I will let you know when the time comes to accompany me on this next step.', 46801), -- Moving On
(66040, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Time is stable once more.', 46801), -- Back to the Future
(66039, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That feels much better!\n\nOh, don\'t worry about Eternus. We\'ve come to a bit of a truce for the moment.', 46801), -- Chromie Time
(66038, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'By the Aspects... This is the Black Empire!', 46801), -- Race Through Time!
(66660, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Are you ready, $n?', 46801), -- On Your Mark... Get Set...
(72519, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The process was not finished but I can more accurately track Chronormu now.', 46801), -- Temporal Two-ning
(66037, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for helping to uphold the timelines... odd as they may sometimes be.', 46801), -- Back to Reality
(70371, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lrgktrr O\'Glrlrlrl!\n\n<The murlocs celebrate your deeds this day!>', 46801), -- Deathwingurlugull!
(66704, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Lrgktrr O\'Glrlrlrl!\n\n<The murlocs appear to be pleased.>', 46801), -- Mugurlglrlgl!
(66035, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Astounding work! \n\nNow, what do you imagine the murlocs of this Murloc World are? I shudder to think...', 46801), -- Murloc Motes
(66033, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Whatever I expected... This is not it.', 46801), -- To the... Past?
(66032, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your journey did not accomplish our goals, but it was a success nonetheless.', 46801), -- Return to the Present
(66029, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The process was not finished but I can more accurately track Chronormu now.', 46801), -- Temporal Tuning
(66031, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve given us some breathing room.', 46801), -- Making Time
(66030, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These brave fighters will be able to bolster their forces once more.', 46801), -- Resistance Isn't Futile
(66028, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We need to find Chromie and Eternus before more damage can be done to this time.', 46801), -- To the Future!
(70040, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If we work quickly, I believe we may be able to catch her.', 46801), -- Tumbling Through Time
(65962, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Eternus and Chromie have fallen through space and time. We must retrieve them at all costs!', 46801), -- The Never-Final Countdown
(65938, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That\'s the second largest time elemental I\'ve ever seen! I knew I should have packed my S.E.L.F.I.E Camera today.\n\nOh well! I\'ll just stop by this moment again on my next day off.', 46801), -- The Once and Future Team
(66646, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work! Usually I am against killing time, but today is an exception.', 46801), -- Quelling Causalities
(65948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work!\n\nYou should be cooking with more than enough time juice to release the Wardens now!', 46801), -- Cracks in Time
(65947, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It worked? I\'m not surprised... not entirely, at least!', 46801), -- Time-Locked Timewalkers
(65935, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'About time! Eternus might look frozen in that bubble, but she\'s struggling with all her might to get free.', 46801), -- Catching Up to Chromie
(66087, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A Timewalker\'s staff is crucial to shepherding time. Sometimes a gentle prod is all that is needed. Other times, firmer action is required. This should be enough to mitigate the instability in this area for now. \n\nWhile there is still more work to be done, your companions are eager to assist up at the temple. I will ensure the area down here is supported while you all go ahead.\n\nGood luck.', 46801), -- Closing Time
(66084, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With these samples, we will have a better understanding of how and why these timelines are intersecting with ours.\n\nThank you for your assistance.', 46801), -- Times Like These
(66085, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it! Right?\n\nOkay maybe there was a wrinkle or two--nothing Dante needs to know about. Also, an unexpected visitor..\n\nStill, overall I would say that went pretty well.', 46801), -- If We Could Turn Back Time
(66083, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was quite unexpected! As you can see, there are many dangers that come with wielding time energy.\n\nI do wish there was time to examine the effects of your little hiccup, but there are more important matters.', 46801), -- Feels Like the First Time
(66082, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This staff has been through a lot, but it should be fully functional again.\n\nThank you, $c.', 46801), -- Time in a Bottle
(66081, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. \n\nNow the forest can try to recover, and the Timewalkers have extra some extra energy.', 46801), -- Time is Running Out
(70136, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, for recovering all that valuable equipment $c.', 46801), -- Haven't Got Time For the Pain
(66080, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I knew somebody would come around... eventually!', 46801), -- Temporal Difficulties
(66320, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello! ... again? I think?', 46801), -- The Flow of Time
(66252, 1, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Eranog joined the Primalists? Flame and Scale, this is a terrible development!\n\nHowever, you were able to prevent them from taking South Hold Gate.\n\nThat is no small feat. I appreciate your service to Valdrakken, $n. It will not be forgotten.', 46801), -- Reporting In
(66251, 1, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'With their leader dead these Primalists should be easy for reinforcements from Valdrakken to clear out.', 46801), -- Fire Fighter
(66250, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Damn it all! The commander was behind this? I cannot believe he would betray us like this.', 46801), -- Where's The Chief?
(66249, 1, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n! That should take some heat off us. \n\nKeep your weapon in hand though, we are not done yet.', 46801), -- Clear the Sky
(66248, 1, 603, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What is this? Rope? There is no time to make a net!\n\nWait... I have an idea. There are some old weapons that we could use with these... \n\nGood eye, $n! These are perfect!', 46801), -- Tying Things Together
(66247, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good find, $n! These should be useful.', 46801), -- Slightly Used Weapons
(66245, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Their memories will be honored.', 46801), -- Remember the Fallen
(66169, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Great work, $c. Those monsters deserve every bit of pain you gave them twice over!', 46801), -- Vengeance, Served Hot
(66246, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This... pains me to hear... but I understand. Thank you, $c.', 46801), -- The Fog of Battle
(66167, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my thanks, and my apologies, stranger. In the heat of battle it is difficult to distinguish a friend from a foe, and there are plenty of foes around.', 46801), -- Southern Exposure
(66163, 11, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. Let this serve as a notice that the Primalists will never be welcome in Valdrakken!', 46801), -- Nowhere to Hide
(66166, 378, 378, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, the Primalists are up to something in the south and soldiers have not been arriving from South Hold Garrison... This does not sound good $n. That does not sound good at all.', 46801), -- Eyes and Ears
(70880, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hello there. Can I offer you a fork? Or maybe some tea?\n\nIt is a pleasure to see so many in Valdrakken. I am sure you will aid us admirably. If you find yourself in need of the knife to match your fork, let me know and we will trade!', 46801), -- To Cook With Finery
(66159, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Raszageth! She is attempting to find them... This is profoundly disturbing news.\n\nWe do not know where her Primalists will be next. Our city must be protected from her chaos.', 46801), -- A Message Most Dire
(66244, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Valdrakken, $n. Kalecgos says there is news about the Azure Span.', 46801), -- To Valdrakken
(66015, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Oathstone is empowered once more. There is much to do... but the Azure Span is at least returning to what it once was.', 46801), -- The Blue Dragon Oathstone
(70041, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Raszageth has fled, Vakthros is stabilized... and more blue dragons have arrived.\n\nI think we can rest for a moment now.', 46801), -- The Storm-Eater's Fury
(66009, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good to see you adventurer. Time is of the essence!', 46801), -- In Defense of Vakthros
(66007, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. Now it\'s time to show the Primalists the true might of the Aspect of the blue dragonflight!', 46801), -- Free Air
(65977, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have my thanks. We cannot forsake anyone in this fight.', 46801), -- Kirin Tor Recovery
(65958, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That orb is brimming with power! That will be perfect for what\'s next.', 46801), -- Primal Power
(65943, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good work, some of their forces are diverting from above.', 46801), -- Primal Offensive
(65944, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That should slow them down a bit. It seems I\'m getting a bit rusty compared to the fight with the Burning Legion...', 46801), -- Lava Burst
(66647, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is it! Hold onto it... you\'ll need it for what\'s next.', 46801), -- Elemental Unfocus
(65887, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is worse than I could have expected. There\'s no time to lose.', 46801), -- To the Mountain
(65886, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I saw Kalecgos and Khadgar go towards the mountains a moment ago. We\'re holding our own against the Primalists here, but we can always use more help!', 46801), -- To Rhonin's Shield
(66027, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We need to move, $n.', 46801), -- Calling the Blue Dragons
(65911, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I never expected to learn so much from the tuskarr. I think I\'ll visit when I can, and maintain those bonds of friendship.', 46801), -- Azure Alignment
(65850, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Kalecgos looks distant.>', 46801), -- The Cycle of the Sea
(66210, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your friend is very inquisitive! Does he ever take a moment to relax?', 46801), -- Gather the Family
(65849, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m so glad you have come to join us. \n\nI must ask you to be patient, however. There is still much to be prepared for the ceremony.', 46801), -- To Iskaara
(65847, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We did it. Great work, $n. Breathe the fresh air again!\n\nWith this ley line restored, and Khadgar finishing up on the one in the tower, the Oathstone should be ready to claim. I must return to the Azure Archives shortly.', 46801), -- Realignment
(65848, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You did well, hero, thank you. \n\nThat tree was probably not their only pool of decay, but it was the riskiest one for the tuskarr and this ley line. With it gone, this area may be able to recover. It will take time, but it will heal. \n\nI\'m glad we were able to give the spirits of those tuskarr some peace.', 46801), -- Tome-ward Bound
(65844, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Gnolls can be fascinating creatures! They\'re not evil, only wild. And very dumb. \n\nKilling them is a shame, but the decay helps no one. And we can\'t let them hurt our family.', 46801), -- Cut Out the Rot
(65845, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So they all chose to lend their power to my totem? \n\n<Brena squeezes her eyes shut in sorrow.> \n\nThank you, my friends. We will use the strength of your spirits well. The gnolls will not reach Iskaara.', 46801), -- Echoes of the Fallen
(65846, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What were they doing with these? Using them as back scratchers?!\n\n<Kalecgos pinches the bridge of his nose.>\n\n...I suppose we should be grateful they didn\'t figure out their true potential.', 46801), -- Ley Litter
(65838, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You may want to cover your mouth. You don\'t want to breathe in the decay.', 46801), -- Breaching the Brackenhide
(66026, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Just standing here, I can feel the dread of this forest wash over me. Something is deeply wrong here. \n\nI\'m beginning to regret sending our best fighter back to Iskaara.', 46801); -- Urgent Action Required
INSERT INTO `quest_offer_reward` (`ID`, `Emote1`, `Emote2`, `Emote3`, `Emote4`, `EmoteDelay1`, `EmoteDelay2`, `EmoteDelay3`, `EmoteDelay4`, `RewardText`, `VerifiedBuild`) VALUES
(65869, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'This is truly a tragedy... but at least we can follow the clues.\n\nWe are getting closer to the source of this rot.', 46801), -- Another Ambush
(66239, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As I feared, they were attacked as well.', 46801), -- Spreading Decay
(65870, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Elder Poa looks approvingly at the supplies you\'ve recovered.>\n\nThe Iskaara tuskarr will hunt again.', 46801), -- Supplies!
(65872, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'We have never seen rot take on a form like this.\n\nThis is troubling.', 46801), -- Ill Gnolls with Ill Intent
(65873, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, '<Brena recoils in disgust as she accepts the totem.>\n\nKargpaw was always violent, but he was also a coward. He and his band never attacked us if we traveled in large numbers.\n\nSomething has changed... and this totem is behind it.', 46801), -- Leader of the Shadepaw Pack
(65871, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Hanu wrinkles her cheeks and shoots a tusky grin at Norukk.>\n\nI\'m beyond relieved that Norukk made it out alive. We will mourn those we lost once we return to Iskaara.', 46801), -- Gnoll Way Out
(65866, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. It will be safer for Brena to make her way here.', 46801), -- Snap the Traps
(65867, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, 'Good, you did what I could not. \n\nBut there is another gnoll leading the Shadepaw... more terrifying than the three you encountered.', 46801), -- Howling in the Big Tree Hills
(65868, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 500, 0, 0, '<Hanu\'s nose crinkles.>\n\nUgh... slathered in slobber.\n\nThey will have to suffice for the chieftain\'s memorial.', 46801), -- Those Aren't for Chewing
(65864, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The gnolls were ruthless in their assault.\n\nThey hit us hard and fast and took everything that wasn\'t nailed down.', 46801), -- Catch the Caravan
(66699, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Brena is your best bet.', 46801), -- Ask the Locals
(65855, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The tuskarr? There are a number of tuskarr merchants and travellers who pass through here.', 46801), -- Aiding Azure Span
(65854, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to be back... or reactivated, as it were. \n\nThere is much to do, and I am glad to give whatever aid I can.', 46801), -- Reclaiming the Oathstone
(65751, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Fine work! I can feel the ley lines beneath this place beginning to heal. We\'re almost done.', 46801), -- Platform Adjustments
(65752, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Kirin Tor will ensure these archives are properly cared for when this is finished. Thank you for your aid.', 46801), -- Arcane Annoyances
(65852, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It\'s a bit worse up here than I had anticipated!', 46801), -- Straight to the Top
(65709, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. It seems these runes are able to transport us to the top of the archives.\n\nI believe that may be where our last problem resides...', 46801), -- Arcane Pruning
(65702, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work. The creations here are already being soothed with just this amount of unstable arcana removed.', 46801), -- Driven Mad
(65689, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let\'s get to work. It\'s imperative to reclaim the Azure Oathstone.', 46801), -- The Many Images of Kalecgos
(65688, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Khadgar is wise to redirect his efforts towards the Primalists.\n\nBut now... we\'ve got a lot of work to do here.', 46801), -- Meeting Kalecgos
(67036, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am relieved that the attack was repelled... but it seems we will need to figure out a plan to help Kalecgos in the Azure Archives.', 46801), -- Wrath of the Kirin Tor
(67033, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. I\'ll begin the ritual to fix this in a moment.', 46801), -- Assemble the Defenses
(67035, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What a relief! To lose all that knowledge... I could not bear the thought.', 46801), -- Preservation of Knowledge
(66228, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, $n. Good to see you...\n\nHold on... do you feel that?', 46801), -- Camp Antonidas
(65686, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '. You must be a dracthyr. \n\nThe Kirin Tor could use your aid, however some of your allies a', 46801), -- To the Azure Span
(66340, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hail adventurer! I\'m glad our call for help reached you.', 46801), -- Into the Azure
(66783, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that our bonds are renewed, nothing can stand in our way. By wind and wing, so be it.', 46801), -- Renewal of Vows
(66336, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the Ancient Bough. You stand before the Emerald Oathstone of the green dragonflight.', 46801), -- The Isle of Emerald
(66337, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'At last, it is done. Our sacred isle is safe once again. Thank you for all you have done for my kind, $n.', 46801), -- Stormbreaker
(66335, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will remain forever grateful that the dragons were on our side during this battle.', 46801), -- Deconstruct Additional Pylons
(66784, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Now that we have cut off our enemy\'s reinforcements, the battle will enter its final stage. Great work, $n.', 46801), -- Starve the Storm
(66333, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good riddance to those awful weapons. May no other dragon suffer as Solethus did.', 46801), -- Justice for Solethus
(66331, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our enemies are one step ahead of us. Do not despair. Our resolve is as strong as our alliance. Prepare yourself, $n.', 46801), -- The Primalist Front
(70220, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'My dragonflight is ready, then? Good. We will confront our enemies with everything we have.', 46801), -- Shady Sanctuary
(66344, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have arrived, mortal. Welcome to the Emerald Gardens.', 46801), -- With the Wind at Our Backs
(66328, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our ancestors said the green dragons were tempered and wise. We are fortunate they restrained their anger long enough to hear our side of the story.\n\nNow that we know the Primalists and Nokhud are our common enemy, it is time to take them down.', 46801), -- Green Dragon Down
(66329, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will not rest until Balakar answers for the crimes he committed here today. The slaughter of my people, the blasphemy against Ohn\'ahra, the treachery against our ancient ally....\n\nVengeance will have to wait. There are more pressing matters. We must help the green dragons.', 46801), -- Blowing of the Horn
(70244, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'What are they doing to Ohn\'ahra? Balakar and Koroleth will pay dearly for this!', 46801), -- Nokhud Can Come of This
(66327, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We are too late. The Nokhud have overrun the Horn of Drusahl and slaughtered my people. \n\nThis act of aggression will not go unanswered.', 46801), -- Chasing the Wind
(66259, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is dire news, $n, but we cannot lose focus. We are bruised but not beaten.', 46801), -- A Storm of Ill Tidings
(66258, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We took quite a tumble. We\'re lucky to be alive.', 46801), -- Oh No, Ohn'ahra!
(66256, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'After all Ohn\'ahra has done for us, we must do all we can to help her children. Thank you, $n.', 46801), -- Eagle-itarian
(66257, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m sure there\'s more out there, but we destroyed what we could. Hopefully, this will at least slow them down.', 46801), -- Fowl Sorcery
(66242, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I don\'t want to spill blood, but the Nokhud must be stopped.', 46801), -- Weather Control
(66236, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Balakar and these Primalists have trampled on our most sacred beliefs.', 46801), -- Catching Wind
(66225, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So many totems. So many fallen mystics.', 46801), -- Toting Totems
(70195, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'So, we are at war with both the Nokhud and the Primalists. Now it is even more critical that we get Ohn\'ahra and the dragons on our side.\n\nThank you for your assistance, $n, and thank you for saving Altan.', 46801), -- Taken By Storm
(66224, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I barely escaped that ambush with my life. I\'m afraid my fellow mystics weren\'t so lucky....', 46801), -- Mystic Mystery
(66254, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Still nothing. Not even a sigh from Ohn\'ahra.', 46801), -- Pessimistic Mystic
(70229, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Who are you? Did Ohn\'ahra send you?', 46801), -- Boku the Mystic
(66222, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I did not wish to cause a panic, but the people must be ready. Clan Nokhud is not known for mercy.', 46801), -- The Calm Before the Storm
(66201, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Jebotai reads the message. His face grows more and more concerned.>', 46801), -- Hooves of War
(66025, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The very lifeblood of the Maruuk is in danger.', 46801), -- The Nokhud Threat
(66023, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The path they have chosen is now stained with blood.\n\nScout Tomul tried to warn us this might happen. She may have further suspicions.', 46801), -- Trucebreakers
(66024, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Balakar was an easy target for Koroleth\'s corrupting influence.\n\nThe storm has arrived.', 46801), -- Covering Their Tails
(66022, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That traitorous fool.\n\n<Akato spits on the ground.>', 46801), -- The Khanam Matra
(66948, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'More friendly faces are welcome indeed.', 46801), -- The Emissary's Arrival
(66969, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<As Sansok Khan signs, Okir vocalizes for her.>\n\nWhile there are many clans of various sizes throughout the plains, Shikaar, Teerai, Ohn\'ir, and Nokhud hold the most power.', 46801), -- Clans of the Plains
(66019, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our ancestors risked much for our future. It is right to invite them to gather alongside us.', 46801), -- Honoring Our Ancestors
(72429, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I look forward to seeing how you contribute to the Maruuk.', 46801), -- Orientation: Maruukai
(66020, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A betrayal threatens Ohn\'ahra herself. We must stand tall, $n. Now is a time for allies.', 46801), -- Omens and Incense
(66021, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Nokhud prefer brute strength and power over all else.\n\nWe do not see eye to eye on many things.', 46801), -- Unwelcome Outsider
(66017, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to be back with my clan.', 46801), -- Clan Ohn'ir
(66018, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I have the great unpleasantness of introducing you to Bahir, one of Balakar Khan\'s thugs.', 46801), -- Clan Nokhud
(66016, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome, outsider.', 46801), -- Clan Teerai
(65806, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to Maruukai.', 46801), -- Maruukai
(66848, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The storm is an omen of grim portent. Trouble is brewing.', 46801), -- Omens on the Wind
(65805, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. I will use these materials to interpret her song.', 46801), -- Connection to Ohn'ahra
(65940, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I sense something on the wind.', 46801), -- By Broken Road
(70185, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Tomul looks the pelt over before offering a small nod.>\n\nYou defeated Konkhular, then. Not bad, two foot. He has evaded our hunters for many moons. His pelt always blended in well with his surroundings. Perhaps now our hunters can use his camouflage to their own advantage.', 46801), -- Mysterious Beast
(65804, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You hunt as strangely as you fight. I hope Aru and Belika observed your technique.', 46801), -- For Food and Rivalry
(65803, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Take a breath, two-foot.', 46801), -- Toward the City
(65802, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Scout Tomul looks over the gathered provisions.>\n\nEverything seems to be in order.', 46801), -- Supplies for the Journey
(65801, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 300, 0, 0, 'The rest of our attending clan has already traveled to Maruukai to prepare our site. The caravan from this outpost will be the last to arrive.', 46801), -- Making Introductions
(70174, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sansok Khan gives you a slight nod.>', 46801), -- The Shikaar
(65783, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You outsiders seem to have a habit of meddling in the affairs of others.', 46801), -- Welcome at Our Fire
(65780, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are a more formidable fighter than I assumed.', 46801), -- Proving Oneself
(65779, 669, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You serve as an envoy of the dragons, then. Times are changing.', 46801), -- Into the Plains
(65795, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We have much to discuss, you and I.', 46801), -- Next Steppes
(65794, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Life Pools are filled once more, in no small part thanks to you.\n\nWith our purpose fulfilled, our oathstone shines once more as a symbol of our calling.', 46801), -- A Charge of Care
(65791, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The future of all the flights is now secure.', 46801), -- Life-Binder on Duty
(66788, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you, $n. I feel like we have a future once more.', 46801), -- Egg-cited for the Future
(66785, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can you believe it?', 46801), -- The Last Eggtender
(65793, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have served admirably, $r.', 46801), -- Black Wagon Flight
(66780, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Surely you back my claim, do you not, $n?', 46801), -- Claimant to the Throne
(66779, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I trust that you understand, now.', 46801), -- Heir Apparent
(66057, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This complicates matters, but I will not be denied what is rightfully mine!', 46801), -- Restoring the Faith
(66354, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The damaged pieces of the Oathstone are repaired! This is only the beginning of what can be accomplished here!\n\nWith the forge re-ignited I can begin the process of crafting new weapons and armor to aid our efforts.', 46801), -- The Spark
(66056, 669, 669, -1, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Very good. Now with the arrival of our Prince, we can begin.', 46801), -- Forging a New Future
(66055, 669, 669, -1, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This looks like all the pieces. I believe we can repair this!', 46801), -- A Shattered Past
(66049, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is a setback, but with your help, I am sure we can repair the Oathstone. Work with Bazentus... make it so.', 46801), -- Obsidian Oathstone
(65939, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent, $n! The djaradin forces are on the run! We control the upper courtyard of the citadel. However, the vaults below may take much longer to secure.', 46801), -- The Courage of One's Convictions
(66044, 457, 457, 457, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done, $n. Sabellian and his forces will hold off the djaradin, while I activate the Oathstone to restore power.', 46801), -- Taking the Walls
(65956, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our advance is pushing them back! All that remains is to breach the gates.', 46801), -- Talon Strike
(65957, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You\'ve proven yourself the true hero of the day, $n.', 46801), -- No Time for Heroes
(66078, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I believe the Blacktalon are prepared for anything.', 46801), -- Sharp Practice
(66048, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I see. I shall consider your evaluation carefully, of course.', 46801), -- Best Plans and Intentions
(72241, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'th, $p.\n\nThe past is the past. Now we must look out for one another. For all dracthyr.Lessons From Our PastNow you know the truth.\n\nT', 46801), -- Lessons From Our Past
(66079, 1, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, champion--your arrival is most fortuitous. With you here now, my plan will certainly succeed.', 46801), -- Wrathion Awaits
(70822, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'ve sent out plenty of scouts since we landed, and a fair number of them haven\'t returned. Could you keep an eye out for them while you\'re exploring? They can often be spotted with our standard issue Expedition Scout Pack. Oh, and if you find any artifacts, deliver them Cataloger Jakes. She\'ll appreciate it.', 46801), -- Lost Expedition Scouts
(66124, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I could not rest until the eggs were safe... this is a relief.\n\nThank you, $p.', 46801), -- Exeunt, Triumphant
(66123, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our queen!', 46801), -- Cut Off the Head
(66121, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Nearly done.', 46801), -- Egg Evac
(66122, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'They may have been our kin, and perhaps we could have approached them as our brethren... but their cruelty leaves no mercy in my heart.', 46801), -- Proto-Fight
(66118, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Lifeshrine stands strong.', 46801), -- Basalt Assault
(66116, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will use every weapon in my arsenal to stop these foes.', 46801), -- The Primary Threat
(66931, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I--\n\nAs much as I wish to follow my queen into battle, I must prove worthy of her trust and protect the Lifeshrine.', 46801), -- Who Brought the Ruckus?
(68799, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back.\n\nThere is much more to do here, but know that you do not take to the skies alone.', 46801), -- Return to the Ruby Lifeshrine
(68798, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you can see, those of us from the different flights have all come together to aid our drakes and yourself. We are all ready for adventure!\n\nOf course, we have not yet convinced... or found... a member of the black dragonflight to join us. But some day they may!', 46801), -- Dragon Glyphs and You
(68797, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'As you explore the Dragon Isles, you will discover even more varied and unique appearances for your dragonriding companion. \n\nBoth of you shall be able to travel in style! As one must, when exploring a new land. How else do you make the best first impression?', 46801), -- A New Set of Horns
(68796, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I suppose I was so eager to show you our foundation here, I may have flown a bit too fast. My apologies!\n\nThere is not  much to look at for the moment as it has been a long time since someone inhabited these terraces. However, we will make them our home once again.\n\nNow, let us introduce you to everyone!', 46801), -- The Skytop Observatory
(70132, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'or listening to me Young One, I appreciated it more ', 46801), -- Stay a While
(65133, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. The rest is now a matter of practice.', 46801), -- How to Use Momentum with Your Dragon
(65120, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'See? That was much better.\n\nIf you start your flights with a dive you will get to where you want to go so much faster.', 46801), -- How to Dive with Your Dragon
(65118, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent work!', 46801), -- How to Glide with Your Dragon
(70061, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good to see our young flying with such joy and liberty in their hearts. Thank you for helping them achieve that.', 46801), -- Training Wings
(68795, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Let us get started.\n\nDo not worry, the fancy maneuvers will come later.', 46801), -- Dragonriding
(66115, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I hope you have grown to appreciate what we do.', 46801), -- The Mandate of the Red
(66114, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'ur face here after what you did. Once, you threatened the future of this dragonflight.\n\nB', 46801), -- For the Benefit of the Queen
(66001, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Is that...?', 46801), -- A Last Hope
(66000, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Our history will survive.', 46801), -- Library of Alexstrasza
(65998, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sendrax is clearly shaken by what she had to do.>\n\nDeath was the only mercy left to those poor whelplings...', 46801), -- Future of the Flights
(65999, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Sendrax pats out a lingering flame on her armor.>\n\nWe\'ve done what we could. What was needed.', 46801), -- Red in Tooth and Claw
(65997, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I haven\'t read anything in the archives about the Primalists stealing dragon eggs before.\n\nThis is bad. Very bad.', 46801), -- Chasing Sendrax
(65996, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Sendrax stopped by and rushed through. That one is a whirlwind.\n\nI like her.', 46801), -- Veteran Reinforcements
(65993, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The djaradin seem to have no shortage of bodies to throw in our way... but perhaps this blow shall give them pause. Well done, friend.', 46801), -- Killjoy
(65995, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A treat! I love seeing into the minds of my enemies. Helps me strike fast, strike true.\n\nLet\'s see...\n\nThe Obsidian Citadel?\n\nNo.\n\nNo!', 46801), -- The Obsidian Citadel
(65992, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That is troubling, to say the least. Yet another reason to fight them.', 46801), -- Blacktalon Intel
(65991, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It does my heart well to hear such good news from Dragonheart Outpost during such a terrible time. The refugees will be safe at the Life Pools.\n\nEven the djaradin would not raise arms against the might of Queen Alexstrasza herself.', 46801), -- Time for a Reckoning
(65989, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Wonderful.', 46801), -- Invader Djaradin
(65990, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We cannot rest yet, but I breathe easier knowing we have rescued them. Thank you.', 46801), -- Deliver Whelps From Evil
(66112, 1, 4, 0, 0, 0, 1000, 0, 0, '<Grun\'s eyes open wide as you hand him the primal cores.>\n\nIncredible! This is the best day of me life!', 46801), -- Always Be Crafting
(65760, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I will take what reinforcements I can get.\n\nWe must act swiftly.', 46801), -- Reporting for Duty
(66111, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'For the Dragonscale Expedition!\n\n<Captain Garrick salutes you.>', 46801), -- Encroaching Elementals
(69965, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Thank you for your help, $p.\n\nIf you ever need items crafted, the Artisan\'s Consortium is here to provide.', 46801), -- Quality Assurance
(69914, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The djaradin have awoken? This is not good, $p...', 46801), -- The Djaradin Have Awoken
(69912, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well then, $p. What do you say? Do you fancy a fight alongside your newfound dragon acquaintances?\n\nI assure you, there is no quicker way to earn their trust.', 46801), -- My First Real Emergency!
(69911, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The embassy is looking better already!\n\nIs every $pr as helpful as you are? I can\'t wait to meet more.', 46801), -- Excuse the Mess
(66101, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Aster breathes a sigh of relief.>\n\nI thought for certain you would plummet to your death from up there. Thanks again for taking the risk so that I was not required to.', 46801), -- From Such Great Heights
(72250, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Head Chef Stacks makes a series of cooking-related sounds and gestures. His whisks whirl! His burners bluster and spit! He bangs on his frying pan with the gravity of a great gong!\n\nThe entire inn applauds his wisdom.\n\nIn watching this elaborate pantomime, you find yourself miraculously better at cooking.>', 46801), -- Dragon Isles Cooking
(72709, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 2000, 0, 0, 'Rae\'ana and I will be traveling with Toddy and Naleidea to our permanent basecamp, once they figure out where that\'s going to be.\n\nFind us there later to see our full catalog.', 46801), -- Funding a Treasure Hunt
(72242, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hi there! Welcome to the Dragon Isles! Hey, you seem like a fellow explosion enthusiast. Can I show you a couple gadgets I\'ve been working on?\n\nI can teach you some new engineering schematics!', 46801), -- Dragon Isles Engineering
(65451, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Boss Magor carefully studies the scales.>\n\nOur artisans will put these to good use. Thank you.', 46801), -- Practice Materials
(69910, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I do not know! As I said, this is my first assignment... Let me think on what to do.', 46801), -- Where is Wrathion?
(72708, 1, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We\'re always looking for more supplies, and I know just what we can do with these.', 46801), -- Dragon Isles Supplies
(66110, 66, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Captain Garrick salutes your approach.>\n\nWarlord Breka proves her honor once again by sending you to me.', 46801), -- Give Peace a Chance
(65453, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That may dissuade them from attacking the expedition camps for a time.\n\nIt\'s eat or be eaten in the Dragon Isles, $p. You\'d do well to remember that.', 46801), -- Primal Pests
(65452, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The dragons are not here to meet us as Ebyssian said they would be...', 46801), -- Explorers in Peril
(65444, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome to the Dragon Isles!', 46801), -- To the Dragon Isles!
(72743, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'There\'s a single piece of copper in your Adventure Guide. It\'s not immediately clear who put it there.\n\nIt\'s not worth much, but hey: free copper!', 46801), -- A Piece of Copper
(64989, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ooh, a porcupine! Some say they\'re prickly, but I think they\'re nice.', 46741), -- Porcupine Soul
(72113, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Greetings, dear friend.\n\nYou have done much to aid us in your time here, but I can sense fate calls you elsewhere.\n\nIn honor of the many souls you have rescued on your journey, and to serve as a guiding light for those you have yet to encounter, please accept this gift. May it serve as a reminder of what wonder life can bring when given a little assistance.', 46741), -- Shapes Beyond the Veil
(63608, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Ah, the hippo. This shape is now yours to call upon.', 46741), -- Hippo Soul
(63708, 1, 6, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'How beautiful. That this Phantasma is able to exist outside of the tower at all is unbelievable. Something is most curious about it\'s nature...further study is needed.', 46741), -- Phantasmagoria
(65063, 1, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. You are awake.\n\n<Viridia coughs to clear her throat.>\n\nWe need an evoker\'s skills right now.', 46702), -- Into the Hive
(65060, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Look at all these wounded...\n\nThere are more Menders inside. We need to help them!', 46702), -- Caldera of the Menders
(65036, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Time runs short. A storm approaches.', 46702), -- Train Like We Fight
(64873, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You are getting the hang of this a lot faster than I was!\n\nBut then, you finished your evoker training. I was hoping to specialize as a diplomat.', 46702), -- Stretch Your Wings
(65615, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Azurathel listens intently as you tell him what you witnessed.>\n\nSo there were beacons placed outside the other creches as well.\n\nOur allies are in peril. We must reach them!', 46702), -- Arcane Intrusion
(64872, 5, 273, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Good. You remember your training.\n\nKeep your head low and your lungs full.', 46702), -- The Fire Within
(64871, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'We will get that rubble cleared and make sure no dracthyr is left behind.\n\nBut first, we need to secure this area.', 46702), -- The Dragon at the Door
(64866, 66, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You healed our people. Well done.\n\nNow to deal with that dragon.', 46702), -- Into the Cauldron
(64865, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This gear is ancient, and the food has turned to dust.\n\nIt makes no sense... those rations should have lasted a lifetime.\n\nWell, we will make do with what we have.', 46702), -- Gear Up
(64863, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Those constructs were animated with blue dragonflight magic. \n\nThe Earth-Warder would never have allowed this!', 46702), -- Arcane Guardians
(64864, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<Azurathel listens to your report.>\n\nMy memories are as broken as yours, $n. But we cannot dwell on that now.\n\nWe need to assess and make a plan.', 46702), -- Awaken, Dracthyr
(43270, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Excellent. Calia Menethil and High Priestess Ishanah are worthy champions. We can trust them to carry out any task we ask of them.', 46702), -- Rise, Champions
(43272, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Your efforts to restore Saa\'ra have not gone unnoticed. As a humble servant of the Sha\'tar, I thank you.$B$BAs leader of the Aldor, it is my duty to safeguard all that is holy. This temple is a beacon of light that must be protected.$B$BYou can count me among your allies, willing to do whatever is necessary to destroy the Burning Legion.', 46702), -- Champion: High Priestess Ishanah
(43271, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well met, $n. It\'s an honor to serve at your side.$B$BI\'m happy to help in any way I can.', 46702), -- Champion: Calia Menethil
(41019, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'An excellent choice! We will do our best to support your efforts on the Broken Isles.', 46702), -- Actions on Azeroth
(40938, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Welcome back, Cardinal. I think you\'ll find we\'ve done quite a job getting this place prepared for you. We should get started immediately.', 46702), -- The Light and the Void
(40710, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'You have demonstrated no small amount of skill in these sorts of tasks.$b$bThat is good, for we will require even more of you if we are to survive this conflict.', 46702), -- Blade in Twilight
(40706, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'A wise choice. My brethren and I stand ready to assist you on your next move, $n.', 46702), -- A Legend You Can Hold
(40705, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Can I take that as a yes?$b$bIf you are ready, I\'d like to get started immediately.$b$bI know you are immensely capable, but let\'s not leave anything to chance!', 46702), -- Priestly Matters
(70049, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Let\'s hope that buys us time before their next incursion.', 46702), -- Calming the Storms
(66458, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Infinite dragons? Their kind always has some kind of plan.\n\nI will inform the Dragon Queen that she will have to find some other way to restore the power of the Aspects.', 46702), -- Legacy of Tyr: Secrets of the Past
(70048, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good you thwarted their attack, at least for now.\n\n<Khadgar examines the motes you brought him.>\n\nHmm, primal elemental energy. I will study this further.', 46702), -- A Primal Threat
(70055, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is outside of my league, magic-wise.\n\nBut I\'ll get it to Khadgar. Continue to push back the Primalist threat.', 46702), -- Sigil of Storms
(70050, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'If you\'re heading into those storms, you\'re going to need all the help you can get.\n\nLucky for you, I\'ve been stocking up on storm-chasing gear for years.\n\nTake a look, and see what fits.', 46702), -- Chasing Storms
(66596, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 're not present to witness Raszageth\'s release as we were, no', 46702), -- Whispers on the Winds
(72240, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I\'m pleased the dracthyr are comin\' with us.\n\nCan\'t wait to challenge that scalecommander to a race on ol\' Wildfeather.\n\nMy gryphon will best his leathery ol\' wings any day!', 46702), -- The Obsidian Warders
(66589, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'That was fast!\n\nEager to get to the Dragon Isles, eh? Me too!', 46702), -- Expeditionary Coordination
(66577, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'o the Dragon Isles beyond the Forbidden Reach. I cannot wait for you to see it!\n\nNow then, I believe that diminutive archaeologist said something about put', 46702), -- Aspectral Invitation
(65436, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'The Aspects\' invitation extends to you as well, friend.', 46702), -- The Dragon Isles Await
(66586, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Infinite dragons? Their kind always has been troublesome.\n\nI will inform the Dragon Queen that she must find another way to restore the power of the Aspects.', 46702), -- Legacy of Tyr: Secrets of the Past
(69992, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'This is outside of my league, magic-wise.\n\nBut I\'ll get it to Khadgar. Continue to push back the Primalist threat.', 46702), -- Sigil of Storms
(69925, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Well done. Let us hope that buys us time before their next incursion.', 46702), -- Calming the Storms
(69923, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'It is good you thwarted their attack, at least for now.\n\n<Khadgar examines the motes you brought him.>\n\nHmm, primal elemental energy. I will take this for further study.', 46702), -- A Primal Threat
(69944, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'These storms are wild, dangerous things. If you wish to confront them, you\'ll want extra protection.\n\nIn my years of hunting, I\'ve gathered many things that helped ward against the wrath of the elements. Perhaps some of them may be of use to you as well.', 46702), -- Chasing Storms
(65439, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Unsettling news indeed, but you had to know of the peril we face.', 46702), -- Whispers on the Winds
(72256, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am pleased to have the dracthyr accompanying us on the expedition.\n\nTheir unique perspective should prove valuable, and learning more of their own history will help them come to terms with their current circumstances.\n\nAs I\'ve said before, history heals every wound.', 46702), -- The Dark Talons
(65443, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I believe this expedition shall be a great success.', 46702), -- Expeditionary Coordination
(65437, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'o the Dragon Isles beyond the Forbidden Reach. \n\nIts wonders will be as new to you as they will be for the Horde.Aspectral InvitationI am hono', 46702), -- Aspectral Invitation
(65435, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'I am grateful you have answered the call. Your courage will be welcome on the journey ahead.', 46702); -- The Dragon Isles Await
